Question: Remove last set of value from a comma separated string in java: :I wan to remove the last set of data from string using java.For example I have a string like A,B,C, and I want to remove ,C, and want to get the out put value like A,B . How is it possible in java? Please help.
Please using this api: StringTokenizer.nextToken.
Answer:<<<api>>>: StringTokenizer.nextToken
<<<code>>>: StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer("A,B,C", ",");
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
    sb.append(st.nextToken());
    if (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
        sb.append(",");
    }
}
String result = sb.toString();
<<<explanation>>>: The StringTokenizer class provides a constructor that accepts a string and a delimiter. It splits the string into tokens based on the delimiter. The hasMoreTokens() method checks if there are more tokens available and the nextToken() method returns the next token. In this code, we are using a StringBuilder to build the string without the last token.
